Three men arrested for possession of illegal firearms and house robbery are expected to appear in the Brits Magistrate s Court on Monday, North West police said. Colonel Emelda Setlhako said the men, aged 37 and 48, were arrested by officers of the Brits police and crime intelligence unit on June 14 in Mamelodi, east of Pretoria in Gauteng. According to the information received the suspects committed the house robbery case in Hebron, she said. African News Agency (ANA)